{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"daff4482-b554-4a82-ade8-a62d98698e01","content":"MSTest v3 dropped support for `.testsettings` files. Here's what I did:\n\n1. **Created `local.runsettings`** — the replacement format. It maps your old settings:\n   - `TestTimeout` → `<MSTest><TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>`\n   - `AssemblyResolution` with `useLoadContext` → `<DeploymentEnabled>false</DeploymentEnabled>` (deployment is off since you were loading from the test directory)\n\n2. **Updated `TestProject.csproj`** — added `<RunSettingsFilePath>` so the `.runsettings` file is picked up automatically by `dotnet test`.\n\nYou can safely delete `local.testsettings` once you've verified tests run correctly. The timeout can also be set per-test via `[Timeout(30000)]` if you prefer attribute-level control.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5cd678d8-00cd-41f4-9770-b3e5569b0d64","outputTokens":209},"id":"06433f73-6913-46f4-9d3c-b8a2e6dc8848","timestamp":"2026-04-05T01:00:16.196Z","parentId":"c063763a-baa9-457b-88b6-21e8ae57dd2f"}
